Description: Shoulder sherd of pottery small amphora or oenochoe; much worn; painted band at top outside; inside streakily glazed. Inscribed.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 342)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 672, no. 303)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.721)
